Blogging Tools

Tools are the backbone of any great blog or blogger. Our team at Blogging Guide assembled the list of resources below to help new writers and content creators identify the essential tools used by most top bloggers. Additionally, all of the tools listed below have been tested by our team, and many are used across our own website.

1. Start a Blog

Read our quick 3 step guide which outlines the basic steps and tools used to create a high powered blog in under an hour.

Step 1. Buy Webhosting & Pick Domain~5 Minutes

The first step in creating a blog is going to Bluehost. Bluehost provides web-hosting services and offers free domains with all their hosting packages. Domain

In this first step you will choose your blog name (domain name) and buy your blog hosting.

  • Step 1. Go to the Bluehost website and click the “Get Started Now” button.
  • Step 2. Select the Basic plan.
  • Step 3. Pick your domain name and enter it into the “New Domain” box.
  • Step 4. Create your Bluehost account.
Try Bluehost and Get a Free Domain!

Step 2. Launch WordPress Website~10 Minutes

After you log in to the account, Bluehost will offer a 4-step process to help you create a blog. Instead, scroll down and choose the “Skip this step” button (we will install our own theme later).

Once you click the “Skip the step” button you will be taken to your Bluehost account page.

After you click the “Launch My Site” button, your blog will go live! Bluehost will install WordPress automatically. Once the install is complete click the blue “WordPress” button to be logged-in to the administrator area of your blog.

If you already have hosting, or your own domain, my recommendation would be to use EasyWordPress.

Try Easy WordPress!

Step 3. Customize and Design Website~30 Minutes

Next you are going to choose a WordPress Theme for your website.

To do this, go to the Elegant Themes website. Elegant Themes offers the WordPress Theme, Divi, which you will be installing on your site. Click on the “Pricing” button in the upper right hand corner of the screen. Using our promotional link, you will see two options:

$89 per Year or $249 for Lifetime Access. Regardless of which option you choose you will be offered a free 30 day trial, allowing you to test Divi absolutely risk free.

Next, download the Divi theme. Upload this theme to WordPress and install it. You will now have the infrastructure in place to create an awesome blog.

Try Divi Risk Free for 30 Days!

2. Popular Tools

Comprehensive reviews of the most popular blogging tools among top content creators.

BlueHost| Affordable Webhosting

Bluehost is one of the largest website hosting providers and powers millions of websites, at some of the lowest prices online, while still remaining user friendly.

Medium Article Title Capitalization Tool

Blogging Guide’s custom capitalization tool automatically formats article titles and subtitles so that they meet the Medium curation requirements.

Adobe Acrobat DC | Create & Edit PDFs

Adobe Acrobat DC is the must have software have for writers and creatives, since it allows you to create, edit, view, sign, fill, and format PDFs.

Fiverr | Affordable Freelance Work

Fiverr is one of the best platforms to find affordable online contractors, specializing in SEO, graphic design, video transcription, writing, and more!

Unsplash | Free Images & Pictures

Unsplash is a compilation of beautiful free images & pictures, that can be used for any purpose or project. Check out Blogging Guide’s free image collections.

Shutterstock | Stock Images, Photos & Videos

Shutterstock give bloggers access a library with more than 320 million images. Click here to get 20% off your first Shutterstock order!

NameCheap | Buy Domains & Create Websites

NameCheap is the perfect balance of affordability and ease of use. You can easily register a domain name, or build a custom WordPress website with EasyWP.

Grammarly | Compose Mistake-Free Writing

From grammar and spelling to style and tone, Grammarly helps you eliminate errors and find the perfect words to express yourself.

Signal | Auto-Tweet Your Articles

Signal is a tool that auto tweets your article links on repeat. This allows writers to spend more time writing and less time on social media marketing.

3. Design Tools

Comprehensive reviews of the top design tools used by bloggers to create article featured images, source stock photos, design their website, and more.

Canva | WYSIWYG Graphic Design

Canva is our top recommended graphic design tool. Create stunning blog images, infographics, and social media posts, in seconds, without coding.

Adobe Spark| Create Stunning Graphics

Get 20% off Adobe Spark by using this link! Create attention-grabbing graphics, videos and social posts, with design guidance from Adobe.

Divi Themes | WordPress Themes

Divi Themes is the best source of custom themes for your WordPress website. Most are drag-and-drop templates and most are visually stunning!

Visme | WYSIWYG Graphic Design

Visme helps bloggers and designers create and share beautiful on-brand presentations, infographics and other visual communications for your team.

Elementor | WordPress Website Builder

Elementor allows anyone to create beautiful sites and pages  on WordPress, using an intuitive drag and drop interface. One of the most popular site builders.

SimpleSlides | Custom PowerPoint Slides

SimpleSlides offers a large library of editable custom PowerPoint slide, infographic, and chart templates. Pay once for lifetime access.
